  Source:
    Title: Kwannon Sutra
Tags:
  - Beauty-Peace=The Surface Of The Waters=Dominating the Waters
  - 385
Glossary:
  - Term: Kwannon
    Description: A Bodhisattva (skr. Avalokitesvara) whose name is
      much invoked in Japan.
---
If drifting in the vast ocean a man is about to be swallowed up by the Nagas,
fishes, or evil beings, let his thought dwell on the power of Kwannon, and the
waves will not drown him.
